{% comment %}
  Champagne de Lossy — page-load intro (mirrors the reference site)
  Adds a `page-loaded` class to <html> on window load (with a fallback), then:
    - the hero curtain slides up (see custom-slideshow.liquid)
    - the header slides down from the top + fades in (after the hero reveals)

  NOTE: when the header is sticky the theme sets `#header-group { display: contents }`,
  which has no box — so transforms/animations on #header-group do nothing. We
  animate its children (`#header-group > *`) instead. No fill-mode "forwards",
  so the sticky header keeps working afterwards. Skipped for reduced-motion;
  not rendered in the theme editor (see theme.liquid).
{% endcomment %}

<script>
  (function () {
    function loaded() { document.documentElement.classList.add('page-loaded'); }
    if (document.readyState === 'complete') loaded();
    else window.addEventListener('load', loaded);
    // fallback so nothing stays hidden if 'load' is slow/never fires
    setTimeout(loaded, 2500);
  })();
</script>

<style>
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
    /* keep the header hidden until the page has loaded */
    html:not(.page-loaded) #header-group > * { opacity: 0; }

    /* then slide each header row down from the top + fade in, after the hero
       curtain has lifted (~1.1s). No fill-mode forwards -> sticky-safe. */
    html.page-loaded #header-group > * {
      animation: cdlHeaderDown 0.7s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1) 1.1s backwards;
    }

    @keyframes cdlHeaderDown {
      from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-101%); }
      to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
    }
  }
</style>
